The Itaewon Halloween accident occurred on October 31, 2020 in Seoul, South Korea. A 21-year-old U.S. soldier, who was driving under the influence of alcohol, drove his vehicle onto the sidewalk in the Itaewon district of Seoul, hitting and killing two South Korean pedestrians and injuring three others. The incident sparked public outrage and calls for accountability from the U.S. military and South Korean authorities.